This place was perfect for a late night pick me up. My husband and I flew in late from London and I was so hungry. We found this place located close to our flat. The ambiance was nice and chill. The menu was creative and the food was delish. I had the hummus with beets and toast and sea bass/spinach/balsamic vinegar salad. Light but filling. The bartender was nice enough to accommodate us since we came a little bit after the kitchen closed. We will def come back as the dessert options sounded creative and yummy. Nice ambiance and good eats!
